text: Rural lane in Drumragh Drumragh is a civil parish and townland in County Tyrone, Northern Ireland, on the right bank of the River Drumragh. Today, it is within the county town of Omagh. It has a Roman Catholic church;Drumragh Parish and a Church of Ireland one.Ireland Anglican ==References== Category:Civil parishes of County Tyrone Category:Omagh
